<h1>Problem 28 - 2016 IMO, P1 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Triangle \(BCF\) has a right angle at \(B\). Let \(A\) be the point on line \(CF\) such that \(FA=FB\) and \(F\) lies between \(A\) and \(C\). Point \(D\) is chosen so that \(DA=DC\) and \(AC\) is the bisector of \(\angle{DAB}\). Point \(E\) is chosen so that \(EA=ED\) and \(AD\) is the bisector of \(\angle{EAC}\). Let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(CF\). Let \(X\) be the point such that \(AMXE\) is a parallelogram (where \(AM \parallel EX\) and \(AE \parallel MX\)). Prove that \(BD,FX\) and \(ME\) are concurrent.</p>
